DIV2.P:
MINE host was one of those geniuses, who, like MACKLIN's Sir Pertinax Mac Sycophant, depended more upon bowing than on education and natural abilities,
he could ne∣ver stand straight in the presence of a guest;
and to the pliability of Sir Pertinax, he ad∣ded the complaisance of SHAKESPEARE's Po∣lonius, being ever of the same opinion with the person he conversed with, unless that person was his wife, or one of his servants; and these he eternally contradicted, whe∣ther they were right, or whether they were wrong.—
